			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">CHAPTER 2: Dark Hunt (Sicarius)
<br />

<br />
The first rays of morning sun came through the window, waking him from light slumber. Suddenly, there came a knock upon the front door. The man grabbed his sword from beneath his pillow and headed towards it. "Who is it?" the man asked through the thick oak.
<br />

<br />
"It is I, Anderus, Sir Sicarius' page. I have an urgent message, please let me in, Sir Julian." 
<br />

<br />
Julian opened the door, allowing Anderus entry. "What is so urgent, Anderus, that cannot wait until the sun has fully risen?" 
<br />

<br />
The page licked his lips and handed Sir Julian a letter, his hands shaking with excitement. "Tis a missive from Empiriana, it bears the official seal of His Majesty, the King!"
<br />

<br />
Julian took the offered parchment and looked at the red wax seal. There was no mistaking the Royal Seal Of Empiriana. Anderus had heard many wondrous tales of adventure about this land from Sir Sicarius, the knight he served and an Empiriana native. Sicarius was always filling the boy's head with tales of riches and glory, but never with the danger one must face to get these things. Julian was sure that Sicarius' policy of 'Ignorance is Bliss' would one day cost Anderus his life. "Thank you young Anderus, I will tell you all about it once I know of this urgent news."
<br />

<br />
With that Julian helped the page to the door through a shower of, "but, wait, just one sec..." and locked the door behind him. He opened the letter and read: 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">"Dear Sir Julian, I write to thee with a matter of utmost importance! Evil haunts our once peaceful kingdom. Children have begun disappearing in the night. Husbands go to hunt and never come home or upon return find their own family gone. You must help us scourge our land of this evil! Please make haste, Sir, and any reward ye ask for, ye shall receive.
<br />

<br />
Sincerely, King Richard Uther Royal House of Empiriana"</span>
<br />

<br />
Julian studied the sword in his hand. His father had given him this sword on his deathbed, as had his father before him and many fathers past. They had all been Vampire Hunters, like himself. Each generation had learned from the prior and grown stronger. Julian was the best of them all. He stared at the steel blade, bloodstained from countless years of dispatching vampire heads. There was no question of what to do. He threw the King's letter into the fire, grabbed his cloak and gear, and left for Empiriana. In his haste, he failed to notice the shadow that was scurrying to follow him. 
<br />

<br />
Dark grey clouds blocked the setting sun's pale rays in the main square of Empiriana. Cold winds whipped Julian's cloak about him. There was nobody in the streets. Everyone was in the relative safety of their homes, not even daring to be about in the early evening. 
<br />

<br />
Subconsciously, the Hunter's hand rested upon his sword hilt as he threaded the streets of Empiriana's main square. There was no question where to find the source of this evil. Only one place remained that even the boldest adventurers feared and dark rumors abounded of - The Lady Obsydyan's castle in the mountains. Julian didn't believe in the old legend, he was sure it had been a tale his father told him to get him to sleep.
<br />

<br />
The legend claimed that Obsydyan was the most beautiful elfmaid in the entire elven nation, and the next Guardian. She was kidnapped by a vampire with a burning hatred for the elves. It is said that after he turned her, her beauty was only enhanced. Furthermore, any mortal man who laid eyes on her would be too awestruck by her loveliness to attempt to harm her and he would become instantly powerless against her. This was where her main power lie. 
<br />

<br />
As Julian approached the castle, the last thing he thought before entering the dark ruins was, "but that was one hundred years ago - she can't still be here!"<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.redaquarius.com/images/470_Taylah_sig.gif" border="0" />
<br />

