			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">CHAPTER 4: A Life for a Life (sicarius)
<br />

<br />
Julian wasn’t sure if his eyes were open. He thought that they were, but he was not able to see a thing. He had no idea where he was, all he knew was that his hands were bound and he was sitting on a hard, cold stone. He assumed that he had managed to find his way to the dungeon. “Lady…" he croaked.
<br />

<br />
Like a flash flood, the memories of what had happened became to come back to him. He had tried to fight the Queen of the Night and lost. All of a sudden, he realized that his wounds no longer seemed to be troubling him, which is amazing considering he had believed them to be fatal. And he doubted that her Ladyship was a nurse. And why was suddenly referring to her in formal tones?  Odder still, how did he know her name was Obsydyan?  
<br />

<br />
As he was puzzling this, a door swung open, casting a blinding light upon him. He tried to squeeze his eyes closed, to shut out the bright light. A beautiful voice, like a breeze over a pond in the springtime, said "You will no longer suffer the pains of mortal flesh. I have given you the most sacred gift this world has to offer. The gift of life eternal. ” As his eyes began to adjust, he noticed that this blinding light was nothing more than a mere candle. He had never known his eyes to be so sensitive to the light before…
<br />

<br />
Then the reality of what she had done, suddenly hit Julian like a ton of bricks - enslaved him to the very thing he hated most - a vampire's existence. A tidal wave of emotion rolled over him, as he let out a bloodcurdling scream. With a wave of her hand, Obsydyan cut off his vocal cords. “Listen carefully, slave! You are alive only because I have allowed you to be. You will obey my every command, or you will rot with the maggots in your own filth, right where you sit!” With another wave of her hand, she released Julian’s vocal cords. A single tear rolled down the side of Julian's bloodstained cheek, as he mumbled “Better death M’lady. Anything but this…”
<br />

<br />
Obsydyan’s smile held no comfort. “The irony of thy words does truly move me, handsome Julian. There was a time when those exact words were uttered by me, to the member of your bloodline. The very one who damned me to this castle … at the time, I did not appreciate what he had done for me… by sparing my 'life'. Rather a two - way sword if thee will allow the jest. Let me tell thee why I have returned this particular blade to thou, Julian, DawnSlayer no more - now my BloodKin."<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.redaquarius.com/images/470_Taylah_sig.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=42679" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tay's Slinkies</a>
